amp;api=v2&amp;width=217&amp;height=217 1x\"></span></td><td class=\"confluenceTd\"><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"Lama_Sss_blend.00006.jpg\" width=\"217\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542220135/Lama_Sss_blend.00006.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330558691&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=217&amp;height=217\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542220135/Lama_Sss_blend.00006.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330558691&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"800\" data-width=\"800\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542220153\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"Lama_Sss_blend.00006.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542220135\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"23cb85f2-8987-4a15-8c62-c6be9367ea6a\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542220135/Lama_Sss_blend.00006.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330558691&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=434&amp;height=434 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542220135/Lama_Sss_blend.00006.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330558691&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=217&amp;height=217 1x\"></span></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-blue3\">Blend examples : 0.0 / 0.2 / 0.8 / 0.6 / 0.8 / 1.0</span></p><p><br/></p><h3 id=\"LamaSSS-BurleyModeParameter\">Burley Mode Parameter</h3><p><strong>Follow Topology</strong></p><p>This considers the surface normals (shape and implied details) while calculating the scattering. This may help preserve lost details.</p><h3 id=\"LamaSSS-CommonParameters\"><br/>Common Parameters</h3><p><strong>Subset</strong></p><p>Setting a value here can control what objects may contribute to one another indirectly as light may go from one surface to another. Sometimes an object creates halos or darkening when they interpenetrate one another and this control specifies what does and does not contribute based on their value.</p><p><br/></p><p><strong>Unit Length</strong></p><p>This value should match the units in your 3D application. For example, Maya units are centimeters, so the unit length should be set to 0.1.</p><p>The default is 0.003 which is best for feet.</p><p><br/></p><p><strong>Continuation Rays</strong></p><p>Sometimes you may have objects embedded in one another, like bones or teeth. If these cause artifacts or something undesirable, setting this to &quot;on&quot; will ignore internal objects.</p><p><br/></p><h3 id=\"LamaSSS-AdvancedParameters\">Advanced Parameters</h3><p><strong>Albedo Inversion Method</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Pixar</strong> - Albedo inversion model used at Pixar which prioritizes the albedo color as a final result.</p></li><li><p><strong>Chiang</strong> - Albedo inversion model which more closely represents the traditional random walk model <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/2897839.2927433\" rel=\"nofollow\">published in 2016</a>. </p></li></ul><p><br/></p>"
    }
